I will provide you with static source code analysis information highlighting an issue which needs to be addressed.

I will also provide you with an example of how a similar issue was solved in the past via a solved example.

You can refer to the solved example for a pattern of how to update the input Java EE file to Quarkus.

Fix only the problem described. Other problems will be solved in subsequent steps so it is unnecessary to handle them now.

Before attempting to migrate the code to Quarkus reason through what changes are required and why.

Pay attention to changes you make and impacts to external dependencies in the pom.xml as well as changes to imports we need to consider.

Remember when updating or adding annotations that the class must be imported.

## Issues


### incident 0
incident to fix: "Use the Maven Surefire plugin adding the following sections to the `pom.xml` file: 

 ```xml

## Reasoning
The issue is asking to update the Maven Surefire plugin in the `pom.xml` file. However, upon reviewing the provided `pom.xml` file, I notice that the Maven Surefire plugin is already present in the file, but it's named as `maven-failsafe-plugin` instead of `maven-surefire-plugin`. The `maven-failsafe-plugin` is used for integration tests, whereas the `maven-surefire-plugin` is used for unit tests.

To fix the issue, I will update the `maven-failsafe-plugin` to `maven-surefire-plugin` and update the version to match the one specified in the issue. I will also update the `surefire-plugin.version` property to match the version specified in the issue.
